\

\b0 Ensemble is document-oriented.  Each document consists of a window with room for the display of interfaces to four MIDI inputs, four score or MIDI file parts, four chains of note filters, and four instruments.  Each input generates notes from one MIDI input channel and/or one part of the score, and passes them down a chain of one or more note filters.  Each note filter in the chain may perform some modification to the note or alter some process according to its parameters.  Finally, the notes are sent to one or more instruments for realization.  An instrument may perform music synthesis or sound processing on the DSP, send the note out to the MIDI interface, or play a sound file. Documents may be saved and loaded via the main menu. Any number of documents may be created or loaded.  \
\

