\b0 \
Usually, only the active document is connected to MIDI input, the score, and the DSP or sound resources.  However, a document's Settings panel allows the specification of a MIDI program change number to the document.   The main Preferences panel then allows the specification of which MIDI channel Ensemble will listen for program changes on.  If a program change is received on that channel which corresponds to a document, that document is connected.  Documents with no program number or a different program number are disconnected.   If more than one document is assigned the same program number, those documents are always connected in parallel whenever any single one of them is selected.\
\
Since  the active document(s) may be changed during a performance, there is nearly unlimited flexibility in the use of system resources.\

